  "fun_fact": "A highway promises saved time. The Bhaniawala–Jolly Grant–Rishikesh widening in Uttarakhand — about 20 km of NH-7, meant to speed up the run to the airport and Char Dham — will take 4,369 trees, mostly Sal, of which 3,605 are to be cut outright. It also crosses an elephant corridor. Through July 2026 residents have been hugging the marked trees in a deliberate echo of Chipko. <a href=\"https://www.downtoearth.org.in/forests/residents-activists-converge-on-saat-mod-in-dehradun-as-authorities-prepare-to-fell-4369-trees\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Read more</a>",
